Drop a wallpaper at this path and name it `current.jpg`:

  ~/nixos-config/wallpapers/current.jpg

That filename is referenced from modules/stylix.nix. Stylix uses it as the
desktop background and (optionally) as a color hint for derived accents.

Pick something cool-toned — blues, greens, deep purples — to harmonize with
the Tokyo Night Storm palette. The "blue flower + Ignis widgets" screenshot
that started this whole direction lives in ~/Pictures/Screenshots/ from
2026-05-17 if you want to revisit the reference aesthetic.

If you change the filename or extension, update `image = ../wallpapers/...`
in modules/stylix.nix to match.
